.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-ssh_assistant \- Parse `~/.ssh/config` to list named hosts, connect to them quickly by number, or push your public key to a remote host using `ssh-copy-id`.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility ssh_assistant
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Parse `~/.ssh/config` to list named hosts, connect to them quickly by number, or push your public key to a remote host using `ssh-copy-id`.
.SH FEATURES
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBHost listing\fP — reads \fC~/.ssh/config\fP and displays all named hosts with their connection command
.IP \(bu 4
\fBQuick connect\fP — pick a host by number from the list instead of typing the full alias
.IP \(bu 4
\fBKey deployment\fP — runs \fCssh-copy-id\fP to push your public key to any host
.IP \(bu 4
\fBGit host awareness\fP — explains intentional auth-only disconnects from GitHub, GitLab, and Bitbucket
.IP \(bu 4
\fBCustom config support\fP — point the tool at any SSH config file with \fC--config\fP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBInteractive mode\fP — running without arguments lists hosts and prompts for a selection
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
bash _ssh_assistant/_ssh_assistant.sh

bash _ssh_assistant/_ssh_assistant.sh --connect myserver

bash _ssh_assistant/_ssh_assistant.sh --copy-id user@example.com

bash _ssh_assistant/_ssh_assistant.sh --config ~/.ssh/work_config

bash _ssh_assistant/_ssh_assistant.sh --config ~/.ssh/work_config --connect staging
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Option   |   Description
\fC--connect HOST\fP   |   Connect directly to the named SSH host alias
\fC--copy-id HOST\fP   |   Run \fCssh-copy-id\fP to deploy your public key to HOST
\fC--config FILE\fP   |   Use FILE as the SSH config instead of \fC~/.ssh/config\fP
\fC-h, --help\fP   |   Show usage
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH SSH CONFIG FORMAT
.PP
The tool reads \fCHost\fP entries from your SSH config file. Wildcard entries like \fCHost *\fP are ignored — only named hosts are listed:
.PP
.EX
Host myserver
  HostName 192.168.1.10
  User deploy
  IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_ed25519

Host staging
  HostName staging.example.com
  User ubuntu
  Port 2222

Host github
  HostName github.com
  User git
  IdentityFile ~/.ssh/github_key
.EE
.PP
Running the tool against this config produces:
.PP
.EX
  Named hosts found in ~/.ssh/config:

   1)  myserver    (ssh myserver)
   2)  staging     (ssh staging)
   3)  github      (ssh github)
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH GIT HOSTING SERVICES
.PP
When connecting to GitHub, GitLab, or Bitbucket via SSH, the remote end closes the connection immediately after a successful authentication handshake. This is expected behavior — those services do not grant interactive shell access. The tool detects these hosts and explains the disconnect so it does not look like a failure.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH EXIT CODES
.PP
Code   |   Meaning
\fC0\fP   |   Success or user exited the menu
\fC1\fP   |   Invalid host selection, \fCssh-copy-id\fP not installed, or unknown option
